/#
   For an asset (e.g. a reference/benchmark asset), the pricing structure used to price it. Used, for example, to specify that the rateIndex "USD-LIBOR-Telerate" with term = 6M is priced using the "USD-LIBOR-Close" curve.
 #/
record FpML5.confirmation.PricingMethod {
  # The asset whose price is required.
  assetReference : FpML5.confirmation.AnyAssetReference

  # A reference to the pricing input used to value the asset.
  pricingInputReference : FpML5.confirmation.PricingStructureReference

}

assetReference.Doc: The asset whose price is required.
assetReference.Name: assetReference

pricingInputReference.Doc: A reference to the pricing input used to value the asset.
pricingInputReference.Name: pricingInputReference
